Book Description


The big bow Mystery marks a key turning point for the detective novel. Sealed-room mysteries had appeared before, but none so fully exploited its puzzling possibilities. The modern style, which disguises the criminal and lay all evidence before the reader, owes much to Zangwill and his retired police detective George Grodman
